Given this closest pair of points divide and conquer:

```
function closestPair(points):
    if length(points) <= 3:
        return bruteForce(points)

    mid = length(points) // 2
    midpoint = points[mid]

    left_points = points[0:mid]
    right_points = points[mid:]

    left_min = closestPair(left_points)
    right_min = closestPair(right_points)

    min_dist = min(left_min, right_min)

    // Find points in strip
    strip = []
    for point in points:
        if abs(point[0] - midpoint[0]) < min_dist:
            strip.add(point)

    // Sort strip by y-coordinate
    strip.sort(key=lambda p: p[1])

    // Check points in strip
    for i in range(length(strip)):
        j = i + 1
        while j < length(strip) and (strip[j][1] - strip[i][1]) < min_dist:
            min_dist = min(min_dist, distance(strip[i], strip[j]))
            j += 1

    return min_dist
```

